    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="647"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12926: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-16T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 16, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 16—2:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Legation’s 18, January 15, 2 p.m.<note n="72" xml:id="d647fn72">Not
                        printed.</note> Legation has sent the following telegraphic instruction to
                    the Counselor of Legation at Nanking:<note n="73" xml:id="d647fn73">Willys R.
                        Peck.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 15, 6 p.m. Please deliver following communication to the Foreign
                            Office in the form of a memorandum: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>‘In view of alarming reports of the movements and activities of
                                    large forces of alleged Chinese Communist bandits in and around
                                    Szechwan Province, the American Legation is much concerned over
                                    serious menace to the safety of American citizens in that
                                    region, and requests that the National Government will take
                                    prompt and effective action to ensure the full protection of
                                    American citizens and their property in Szechwan and neighboring
                                    areas.’</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Repeated to Hankow for information.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
